<div class="container">
    <div class="space-60"></div>
    <main class="panel-group" id="accordion">
      <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading">
              <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1">What is My Care Compass?</a></h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
              <div class="panel-body">My Care Compass is part of a 6 year research and design project at the W21C Research and Innovation Centre at the University of Calgary, Alberta, Canada. The goal of the project is to learn about patients with multiple chronic conditions and the challenges and issues they face in their day-to-day experiences. We also talked to doctors, specialists, and other health care providers to understand their perspectives on those same issues and challenges. We’ve discovered that patients have needs and concerns that are poorly addressed with existing systems and information. My Care Compass is where we’re realizing our vision of what patients really need on their chronic care journey. </div>
          </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading">
              <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2">Who created My Care Compass?</a></h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
              <div class="panel-body">My Care Compass is the brain child of a team of researchers and designers at the W21C Research and Innovation Centre at the University of Calgary. The W21C works with patients, doctors, health care systems, industry partners, and government organizations to make care better.</div>
          </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading">
              <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse3">My Doctor’s office/local hospital already has an electronic medical record (EMR). Why do I need this?</a></h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapse3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
              <div class="panel-body">There’s a lot of exciting stuff going on in Alberta (and the World) with EMRs and having areas of them for patients to access information too. But those systems have been developed mostly for doctors, or even by doctors, and we believe that patients need more supportive and clearer information and tools than what is there (so far). My Care Compass is envisioned to be different – by putting patients at the centre of what we create and imagine. Our tools and resources are focussed on the patients, not the doctors, and include the information that patients have told us they need, not what doctors think they need.</div>
          </div>
      </div>

